section.section:
There is a Land Reclamation Committee. It consists of the following 13 members:
Two members of the Department, including a chairman of the Committee appointed by the Secretary;
A representative of the soil conservation district of Allegany County;
A representative of the soil conservation district of Garrett County;
Two members appointed by the Governor with the advice and consent of the Senate for 3-year terms to represent the mining industry;
One member who is a representative of Allegany County to be appointed by the Governor, on the recommendation of the Allegany County Commissioners, with the advice and consent of the Senate to represent the local government for a 3-year term;
One member who is a representative of Garrett County to be appointed by the Governor, on the recommendation of the Garrett County Commissioners, with the advice and consent of the House of Delegates to represent local government for a 3-year term;
Two members from the community who do not have any interests in any mining operation, one to be a resident of Garrett County and one to be a resident of Allegany County, appointed by the Secretary for 3-year terms; and
Three members of the Department of Natural Resources appointed by the Secretary of Natural Resources.

text.section:
The Committee may:
Study and recommend surface coal mine reclamation policies, practices, and standards;
From time to time, review the surface coal mining laws, regulations, and policies for the purpose of recommending changes to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of the program;
Review proposed changes to the surface coal mining laws and regulations to provide comments to the General Assembly and the Department;
Review the Department's administration of the surface coal mining regulatory program and the abandoned coal mine reclamation program to determine compliance with the purpose of the subtitles;
Enter on any surface coal mining operation to determine mining and reclamation conditions; and
Recommend research, demonstration, and cost-sharing projects to promote optimum revegetation of surface coal mined lands.
